<Content>run !! Hotel put us last minute in an apartment cross town when we arrived. Said there was a problem with our toilet. We took a train to a bus to a plane, walked 25 minutes in foreign city to find this out. Walked another 15 to apt. to meet employee? with a key. Could smell bug fumigation smell in delux apartment. Two dead cockroaches on the floor. Employee took our credit card inside room and ran it through portable machine. Said transaction did not go through, ripped up receipt. Walked us down to an ATM so we could withdrawl cash! I made him write handwritten receipt. Employee spoke no english, we spoke little spanish. Assured us we would not see double transaction, and of course 5 days later we did. Took us many emails and bank phone contacts to straighten it out. Hotel assures us this was not a 'scam but an oversight. You decide. Finally got credit for additional charges. Did not have any room service over the 3 night stay, no fresh towels, soap or toiletpaper. To the plus side...it was a good location to everything. Price was reasonable. Area appeared safe. 
