<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Triunfo only good as a last resort The Triunfo is a fairly crummy little hotel. We were prepared for small and basic, since we were looking in the budget range. But the Triunfo was extremely noisy (particularly the ancient elevator), incredibly cramped (it was difficult for both of us to stand in the room at the same time, unless one of us was standing right next to the window - essentially, one of us had to be sitting on the bed at all times), dark, not terribly clean, and not terribly hospitable. They also said at the outset that they took credit cards, and then reneged.The rooms do not all have balconies overlooking the Parc Ciutadella, as promised. Ours had a window looking into an internal chute of some kind -so we kept the shade down. The location was OK, but not ideal. We ended up in this hotel only because we were staying for more than a week and every other hotel we tried was booked during part of that time. I would not stay there again. 
